          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Samples were made from spectrograhically pure indium",
                " having purity better than 99.9%.",
                "In the preparation of the target sample, the indium",
                " metal of thickness 3.34 mg/cm2 was deposited onto the",
                " aluminium backing of thickness 6.75 mg/cm2 by vacuum",
                " evaporation technique.",
                "The indium foil was cut into pieces of size 1.5 cm x",
                " 1.5 cm and each of them was glued to an aluminium",
                " frame having a circular hole of diameter 1.2 cm.",
                "These pieces were arranged in a stack.",
                "Aluminium and copper foils were also used in between",
                " the indium foils to get desired incident energy on",
                " each foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 100 cc ORTEC Ge(Li) detector coupled with",
                " precalibrated 4096 analyzer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A computer code ALICE/LIVERMORE-82 was used",
                " for theoretical calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The incident energy with their corresponding",
                " uncertainties are taken from the text of the article."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CRITIQUE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "By Compiler (2013-06-18):",
                " The Bombay Conf. Proc. article gives cross sections",
                " labelled as 115In(a,n)116gSb, 115In(a,n)116mSb and",
                " their sum in a tabulated form. The 115In(a,n)116mSb",
                " is, however, inconsistent with 113In(a,n)116mSb",
                " cross sections compiled in D6209.002 (this entry)",
                " above 30 MeV where the contribution of 115In is",
                " dominant. The compiler sent the question to",
                " A.K.Chaubey on 18 June 2013, and decided to postpone",
                " compilation of the cross sections until the question",
                " is resolved."
              ]
            }
          ],
